component_text: If a book is removed from a shelf because someone finds it offensive then the next person who comes along looking for that book can not access it

Reading expands our vacabulary, at any age

If you are concerned about your children finding books that you do not want them to see then take them to a library with sections
All libraries are broken down in sections
Keep your children in the 'children' section and there should not be any concerns in that area
Once your children get older allow them to roam the library and develope an oppinion on what types of books they enjoy most
